remember what was going

00:26:14.010 --> 00:26:16.150
on in the world 20 years ago

00:26:16.150 --> 00:26:19.650
when the Harry Potter books
were first published in America.

00:26:19.650 --> 00:26:22.140
Luckily my husband David
sterling is a historian

00:26:22.140 --> 00:26:24.670
and has a better
memory than I do.

00:26:24.670 --> 00:26:27.820
He reminded me 20 years ago we
were living here in Washington,

00:26:27.820 --> 00:26:31.730
D.C. about six blocks from
where we are right now,

00:26:31.730 --> 00:26:34.550
while he had a fellowship at
the Smithsonian and I worked

00:26:34.550 --> 00:26:36.120
on a book about amelia ear Hart

00:26:36.120 --> 00:26:38.490
and Eleanor Roosevelt's
friendship.

00:26:38.490 --> 00:26:40.050
Movies like Armageddon,

00:26:40.050 --> 00:26:45.980
saving private Ryan
were at the box office.

00:26:45.980 --> 00:26:48.130
Frank Sinatra died.

00:26:48.130 --> 00:26:50.730
Google became a company.

00:26:50.730 --> 00:26:56.670
Aretha stepped in for
Pavaratti at the awards,

00:26:56.670 --> 00:26:58.910
and sang "none shall sleep,"

00:26:58.910 --> 00:27:03.200
which sounds a little
like a warning.

00:27:03.200 --> 00:27:06.630
President in the White House
around much talk of impeachment

00:27:06.630 --> 00:27:10.240
and a Republican senator
from Arizona had just died.

00:27:10.240 --> 00:27:12.990
The best thing that can
ever be said of anyone is

00:27:12.990 --> 00:27:14.580
that they served
to a cause greater

00:27:14.580 --> 00:27:16.500
than their self-interest.

00:27:16.500 --> 00:27:20.000
Those words were
spoken by John McCain

00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:21.880
at Barry Goldwater's funeral.

00:27:21.880 --> 00:27:24.730
And those are being
spoken by so many others

00:27:24.730 --> 00:27:28.730
as he lies across the street.

00:27:28.730 --> 00:27:31.740
Our lives history itself feel

00:27:31.740 --> 00:27:35.060
like an obstacle course
we're navigating in the dark.

00:27:35.060 --> 00:27:39.080
We stumble from one unimaginable
moment to the next and only

00:27:39.080 --> 00:27:42.190
when we look back we see a path.

00:27:42.190 --> 00:27:46.600
Hindsight is what turns
experience into stories.

00:27:46.600 --> 00:27:48.960
Sometimes the story
feels like a circle

00:27:48.960 --> 00:27:51.960
but that's what human beings do.

00:27:51.960 --> 00:27:54.630
We turn everything into stories.

00:27:54.630 --> 00:27:56.810
As if we had storytelling
in our DNA.

00:27:56.810 --> 00:28:01.390
And sometimes the storyteller
comes along who seems able

00:28:01.390 --> 00:28:05.450
to distill vast and
important ideas into something

00:28:05.450 --> 00:28:08.400
that connects with their
culture and they offer back

00:28:08.400 --> 00:28:12.460
to civilization a reflection
of ourselves, which speaks

00:28:12.460 --> 00:28:15.430
to our needs as individuals
and as a society.

00:28:15.430 --> 00:28:17.560
That's what I think
J. K. Rowling did

00:28:17.560 --> 00:28:19.780
with the Harry Potter books.

00:28:19.780 --> 00:28:24.340
I was a newcomer when
called last Halloween.

00:28:24.340 --> 00:28:27.210
I had only read them for the
first time two years earlier.

00:28:27.210 --> 00:28:31.930
If you haven't read them,
they're good by the way.

00:28:31.930 --> 00:28:34.450
Even though I hadn't
read them myself,

00:28:34.450 --> 00:28:36.830
I loved the phenomenon of them.

00:28:36.830 --> 00:28:39.090
As a former independent
book seller --

00:28:39.090 --> 00:28:42.490
I'm very proud of that fact --
I loved walking by book stores

00:28:42.490 --> 00:28:46.710
at midnight and seeing the vast
lines of families in costume

00:28:46.710 --> 00:28:49.870
and hearing a kind of
excitement for books and stories

00:28:49.870 --> 00:28:52.460
that perhaps hadn't been
experienced by the culture

00:28:52.460 --> 00:28:56.580
as a whole since 19th century
crowds gathered at the docks

00:28:56.580 --> 00:29:00.350
in New York harbor waiting for
copies of the last installment

00:29:00.350 --> 00:29:03.570
of Charles Dickens' "the
old curiosity shop" to find

00:29:03.570 --> 00:29:06.040
out if Nell lived or died.

00:29:06.040 --> 00:29:10.200
I'm not going to spoil it here.

00:29:10.200 --> 00:29:13.140
At last, three years
ago I decided to jump in

00:29:13.140 --> 00:29:15.830
and read the Harry
Potter series myself.

00:29:15.830 --> 00:29:19.330
I was overwhelmed and
became a huge fan.

00:29:19.330 --> 00:29:26.730
Wizards, magic, dragons, giants,
elves, orphans, evil, hypocrisy,

00:29:26.730 --> 00:29:32.330
bravery, tragedy,
betrayal, hope and love.

00:29:32.330 --> 00:29:36.610
Somehow she had taken all the
elements and made something new.

00:29:36.610 --> 00:29:40.450
She put us all at the center of
the most extraordinary narrative

00:29:40.450 --> 00:29:43.470
about someone's life
effects and affected

00:29:43.470 --> 00:29:45.810
by earth shattering events.

00:29:45.810 --> 00:29:48.720
She forced us to
ask big questions.

00:29:48.720 --> 00:29:52.580
What do we do when everything
around us seems hopeless?

00:29:52.580 --> 00:29:55.480
When the people we
most trust die?

00:29:55.480 --> 00:29:58.200
And when the institutions
we most love begin

00:29:58.200 --> 00:30:00.590
to crumble around us?

00:30:00.590 --> 00:30:04.390
In many ways these books remind
us that in the darkest of times,

00:30:04.390 --> 00:30:07.670
it's books themselves
we can turn to for help.

00:30:07.670 --> 00:30:12.520
They remind us that we need
heroes and we can be heroes.

00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:16.570
And maybe unconsciously we
are aware that like books,

00:30:16.570 --> 00:30:21.220
our own lives unfold in
chapters from our infancy

00:30:21.220 --> 00:30:25.640
through our childhood and into
our adulthood and old age.

00:30:25.640 --> 00:30:28.880
Different chapters perhaps
but all the same story.

00:30:28.880 --> 00:30:31.870
I think that's why when I
was asked to draw new covers

00:30:31.870 --> 00:30:34.080
for the books, I knew
right away I wanted

00:30:34.080 --> 00:30:38.370
to do one long epic drawing
that would span all seven covers

00:30:38.370 --> 00:30:41.020
when lined up, a visual
narrative that would try

00:30:41.020 --> 00:30:44.320
to parallel what Rowling
does in the stories.

00:30:44.320 --> 00:30:46.880
I wanted the Dovers to
focus on the relationships

00:30:46.880 --> 00:30:50.640
between the characters,
the queer idea of family,

00:30:50.640 --> 00:30:54.110
non-biologically related people
who you find yourself related

00:30:54.110 --> 00:30:58.820
to through shared interests,
ideas, love and dreams.

00:30:58.820 --> 00:31:02.450
The families that Harry Potter
himself creates are particularly

00:31:02.450 --> 00:31:04.350
complex and beautiful.

00:31:04.350 --> 00:31:06.730
I wanted to draw
these relationships,

00:31:06.730 --> 00:31:09.970
these families in my covers.

00:31:09.970 --> 00:31:12.960
Most of all, I wanted the
main theme of my covers

00:31:12.960 --> 00:31:15.540
to be the battle
between good and evil.

00:31:15.540 --> 00:31:16.840
Since that was the element

00:31:16.840 --> 00:31:18.490
of the books I found
most intriguing,

00:31:18.490 --> 00:31:20.870
and the one I believe is
currently most important

00:31:20.870 --> 00:31:22.170
and relevant.

00:31:22.170 --> 00:31:25.590
The books tell us with the
prospect that Voldemort,

00:31:25.590 --> 00:31:30.140
the embodiment of evil
could win the battle.

00:31:30.140 --> 00:31:32.870
If he wins, what then?

00:31:32.870 --> 00:31:35.910
We get glimpses when
evil gains power.

00:31:35.910 --> 00:31:40.550
One of the characters is
Doris, dresses in bright pink

00:31:40.550 --> 00:31:44.300
and collects cats,
but uses bureaucracy

00:31:44.300 --> 00:31:48.160
to torture those
weak and powerless.

00:31:48.160 --> 00:31:51.550
It's examination of
hypocrisy when people

00:31:51.550 --> 00:31:55.610
in power say they are
helping but hurting others.

00:31:55.610 --> 00:31:59.770
Doris illuminates a corrupted
soul and shows why we must fight

00:31:59.770 --> 00:32:01.900
against anyone like her.

00:32:01.900 --> 00:32:05.920
Up against all this evil
are Harry and his friends.

00:32:05.920 --> 00:32:07.280
They suffer.

00:32:07.280 --> 00:32:09.110
They lose people they love.

00:32:09.110 --> 00:32:10.930
They make mistakes.

00:32:10.930 --> 00:32:15.610
They are young and they fight
heroickicly and suffer greatly.

00:32:15.610 --> 00:32:19.950
But they are undon'ted
and they are together.

00:32:19.950 --> 00:32:22.860
Theirs is a story worth sharing.

00:32:22.860 --> 00:32:26.120
Those here tonight and
those coming this weekend

00:32:26.120 --> 00:32:30.010
for the National Book Festival
understand that empathy,

00:32:30.010 --> 00:32:33.800
love and understanding can be
gained through books as well

00:32:33.800 --> 00:32:35.640
as through the act of reading.

00:32:35.640 --> 00:32:38.210
And children's books were
a lifelong love of reading

00:32:38.210 --> 00:32:40.780
and where empathy begins.

00:32:40.780 --> 00:32:44.640
I think the Harry Potter books
were in their way prescient.

00:32:44.640 --> 00:32:49.060
20 years later, Rowling's
vision of children saving us,

00:32:49.060 --> 00:32:51.210
children stepping up
and pointing the way

00:32:51.210 --> 00:32:55.220
to the future is echoed in the
actions of young people today,

00:32:55.220 --> 00:32:58.980
many of whom are taking to the
streets protesting injustice,

00:32:58.980 --> 00:33:01.480
speaking out, confronting evil.

00:33:01.480 --> 00:33:04.970
These young people were raised
in the spirit of Harry Potter,

00:33:04.970 --> 00:33:06.510
whose frame of reference
for most

00:33:06.510 --> 00:33:10.010
of their lives was leadership
associated with decency

00:33:10.010 --> 00:33:12.210
and intelligence and empathy.

00:33:12.210 --> 00:33:15.700
They are fighting back and
will continue to fight back.

00:33:15.700 --> 00:33:17.540
We must support them.

00:33:17.540 --> 00:33:19.470
J. K. Rowling knew
it was the children

00:33:19.470 --> 00:33:21.480
who will help us win the battle.

00:33:21.480 --> 00:33:24.370
That's why I'm proud to be
here representing Harry Potter

00:33:24.370 --> 00:33:27.980
at the National Book Festival,
where we are reminded now more

00:33:27.980 --> 00:33:30.240
than ever what we
need to celebrate

00:33:30.240 --> 00:33:35.050
and support are good stories,
the endless power of books,

00:33:35.050 --> 00:33:37.160
and the vast bravery
of children.

00:33:37.160 --> 00:33:39.460
Thank you very much.

